{
  "texts": [
    "RV-22 + DWT + SVM has attained 92% validation and 91.8% testing accuracy, while DEV-22 + DWT + SVM is marginally superior to the former, with 92.7% validation and 92.3% testing accuracy.",
    "The SVM's strong classification capabilities on new and unknown data, which enable effective generalization, are evident in the uniformity of performance metrics in training, validation, and testing.",
    "Furthermore, the models exhibit their ability to clearly differentiate between classes, as evidenced by their high AUC scores.",
    "The RV-22 + DWT + SVM exhibits an AUC score of 93.5%, while the DEV-22 + DWT + SVM has an AUC score of 94.3%.",
    "The models guarantee accurate positive case prediction and efficient retrieval of the positives, as their precision and recall are nearly identical."
  ]
}